@startuml ViewAllHistory

actor User
boundary "HistoryPage" as View #lightblue
participant ":historyRoute" as Route #lightblue
control "historyValidation" as Validation #orange
control "historyController" as Controller #lightblue
participant ":historyService" as Service #lightblue
entity "historyModel" as Model #lightblue
database "MongoDB" as MongoDB #yellow

group View History List
User -> View: 1. Click "View History"
activate View
User -> View: 2. Page loads and sends request

View -> Route: 3. GET /api/v1/history
activate Route

Route -> Validation: 4. validateGetHistory(req)
activate Validation

alt Validation Failed
    Validation --> Route: 5. Return 400
    Route --> View: 5.1. Show error
    View --> User: 5.1.1. Display error message
    deactivate Validation
    deactivate Route
    deactivate View
else
    Validation --> Route: 6. Proceed
    deactivate Validation

    Route -> Controller: 7. getHistory(req, res)
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Service: 8. getHistory(userId)
    activate Service

    Service -> Model: 9. viewHistory(userId)
    activate Model

    Model -> MongoDB: 10. Query user history
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB --> Model: 11. Return result
    deactivate MongoDB

    Model --> Service: 12. Return history
    deactivate Model

    Service --> Controller: 13. Return data
    deactivate Service

    Controller --> Route: 14. Send response
    deactivate Controller

    Route --> View: 15. Update UI
    deactivate Route

    View --> User: 16. Show all history
end

deactivate View
@enduml
